workflow.name: Research business leads with Perplexity AI & save to Google Sheets using OpenAI
workflow.description:
Automatically research new leads in your target area, structure the results with AI, and append them into Google Sheets ‚Äî all orchestrated in n8n.

---

## ‚úÖ What this template does
- Uses **Perplexity** to research businesses (coffee shops in this example) with company name + email  
- Cleans and structures the output into proper JSON using **OpenAI**  
- Appends the new leads directly into **Google Sheets**, skipping duplicates  

> **Trigger:** Manual ‚Äî ‚ÄúStart Workflow‚Äù

---

## üë§ Who‚Äôs it for
- **Sales & marketing teams** who need to prospect local businesses  
- **Agencies** running outreach campaigns  
- **Freelancers** and consultants looking to automate lead research  

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è How it works
1. **Set Location** ‚Üí define your target area (e.g., *Hershey PA*)  
2. **Get Current Leads** ‚Üí pull existing data from your Google Sheet to avoid duplicates  
3. **Research Leads** ‚Üí query Perplexity for 20 businesses, excluding already-scraped ones  
4. **Write JSON** ‚Üí OpenAI converts Perplexity output into structured Company/Email arrays  
5. **Split & Merge** ‚Üí align Companies with Emails row-by-row  
6. **Send Leads to Google Sheets** ‚Üí append or update leads in your sheet  

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup instructions
Follow these sticky-note setup steps (already included in the workflow):

### 1) Connect Google Sheets (OAuth2)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Google Sheets (OAuth2)**  
2. Sign in with your Google account and grant access  
3. In the Google Sheets node, select your **Spreadsheet** and **Worksheet**  

Example sheet:  
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MnaU8hSi8PleDNVcNnyJ5CgmDYJSUTsr7X5HIwa-MLk/edit#gid=0  

---

### 2) Connect Perplexity (API Key)
1. Sign in at https://www.perplexity.ai/account  
2. Generate an API key: https://docs.perplexity.ai/guides/getting-started  
3. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Perplexity API**, paste your key  

---

### 3) Connect OpenAI (API Key)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**  
2. Paste your **OpenAI API key**  
3. In the **OpenAI Chat Model** node, select your credential and a **vision-capable model** (e.g., `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4o`)  

---

## üîß Requirements
- A free **Google account**  
- An **OpenAI API key** (https://platform.openai.com)  
- A **Perplexity API key** (https://docs.perplexity.ai)  
- n8n self-hosted or cloud instance  

---

## üé® How to customize
- Change the **Search Area** in the `Set Location` node  
- Modify the **Perplexity system prompt** to target different business types (e.g., gyms, salons, restaurants)  
- Expand the Google Sheet schema to include more fields (phone, website, etc.)  

---

## üì¨ Contact  
Need help customizing this (e.g., filtering by campaign, sending reports by email, or formatting your Google Sheet)?  

- üìß **robert@ynteractive.com**  
- üîó **[Robert Breen](https://www.linkedin.com/in/robert-breen-29429625/)**  
- üåê **[ynteractive.com](https://ynteractive.com)**

parameters.content:
### Research and log new business leads into Google Sheets (Perplexity + OpenAI + Google Sheets)

Automatically research new leads in your target area, structure the results with AI, and append them into Google Sheets ‚Äî all orchestrated in n8n.

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup instructions
Follow these sticky-note setup steps (already included in the workflow):

### 1) Connect Google Sheets (OAuth2)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Google Sheets (OAuth2)**  
2. Sign in with your Google account and grant access  
3. In the Google Sheets node, select your **Spreadsheet** and **Worksheet**  

Example sheet:  
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MnaU8hSi8PleDNVcNnyJ5CgmDYJSUTsr7X5HIwa-MLk/edit#gid=0  

---

### 2) Connect Perplexity (API Key)
1. Sign in at https://www.perplexity.ai/account  
2. Generate an API key: https://docs.perplexity.ai/guides/getting-started  
3. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Perplexity API**, paste your key  

---

### 3) Connect OpenAI (API Key)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**  
2. Paste your **OpenAI API key**  
3. In the **OpenAI Chat Model** node, select your credential and a **vision-capable model** (e.g., `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4o`)  



- üìß **rbreen@ynteractive.com**  
- üîó **Robert Breen** ‚Äî https://www.linkedin.com/in/robert-breen-29429625/  
- üåê **ynteractive.com** ‚Äî https://ynteractive.com

### 2)To set up credentials for the Perplexity API in n8n, follow these steps:

Obtain your Perplexity API key:

Sign in to your Perplexity account at https://www.perplexity.ai/account.
Follow the instructions in the Perplexity API getting started guide to generate an API key: https://docs.perplexity.ai/guides/getting-started.
In n8n:

Go to "Credentials" in the left sidebar.
Click "New credential" and search for "Perplexity".
Select the "Perplexity API" credential type.
Enter your API key in the required field.
Save the credential.

### 1) Connect Google Sheets (OAuth2)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí Google Sheets (OAuth2)**  
2. Sign in with your Google account and grant access  
3. In each Google Sheets node, select your **Spreadsheet** and the appropriate **Worksheet**:  


https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MnaU8hSi8PleDNVcNnyJ5CgmDYJSUTsr7X5HIwa-MLk/edit#gid=0

### 3) Connect OpenAI (API Key)
1. In **n8n ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí New ‚Üí OpenAI API**  
2. Paste your **OpenAI API key**  
3. In **OpenAI Chat Model**, select your credential and a **vision-capable** chat model (e.g., `gpt-4o-mini`, `gpt-4o`, or your configured vision model)
